Package userInterface

Class PatientApptUI

java.lang.Object
userInterface.PatientApptUI
All Implemented Interfaces:
PatientApptInterface
public class PatientApptUI extends Object implements PatientApptInterface
The class implements the PatientApptInterface to provide a UI for managing patient appointments. It allows a patient to view available doctors and time slots, schedule, reschedule, cancel appointments, and view scheduled or past appointment outcomes.

    • selectTimeSlot

      public boolean selectTimeSlot(Scanner sc, String doctorID, Patient patient)
      Prompts the user to select an available time slot for their appointment. It ensures the date and time are valid and checks the doctor's availability. Breaks if wrong format is entered for date and time.
      Parameters:
      sc - A Scanner object for user input.
      doctorID - The ID of the doctor being scheduled with.
      patient - The patient who is scheduling the appointment.
      Returns:
      True if the appointment was successfully scheduled, otherwise false.
